[concept] cluster `user` ambiguous — cluster_crate::domain::User
  confidence 0.75; review members
  if same concept:
    locus accept canonical cluster_crate::domain::User --concept user
    locus accept boundary cluster_crate::api::UserResponse --concept user
  if separate concepts:
    locus accept canonical cluster_crate::domain::User --concept user
    locus accept canonical cluster_crate::api::UserResponse --concept user_userresponse

[layer] domain layer detected, but no paradigms onboarded
  required by BO, ER, FL, RM
  globs: cluster_crate::domain::*
  specify (run for each paradigm you want to onboard):
    locus bo add-domain-path "cluster_crate::domain::*"
    locus fl add-domain-path "cluster_crate::domain::*"
    locus er add-domain-path "cluster_crate::domain::*"
    locus rm add-domain-path "cluster_crate::domain::*"
  or skip these paradigms:
    locus init --acknowledge-empty BO,ER,FL,RM

[feature] no features defined; DG/FO will not fire
  top-level modules: api, domain
  empty public_api means the feature surface is not yet declared, not that every cross-feature import is an architecture bug — DG003 only flags reaches into internals once features list a public_api
  define:
    locus dg define-feature --name api --module "api::*" --public-api "api::*"
    locus dg define-feature --name domain --module "domain::*" --public-api "domain::*"
    # (FO mirrors DG features once these are accepted)
  or skip:
    locus init --acknowledge-empty DG,FO

